$(H2 Float)

$(P
Basic type $(B float) is for a programmer to operate with what
in math called $(I real) numbers. Since big procentage of all
computer programs is engineering programs that do calculations,
let us have a closer look at this type.
)

$(P
Value can be assigned to $(B float) variable using literal
number with decimal point:
---
float pi = 3.14;
---
Literals may have exponent:
---
float pi = 0.0314e2;
---
)

